-- Portugal Galp recovers from early losses after ENI sells stake
-- 
-- Fri Mar 28, 2014 06:04AM EDT
-- None



LISBON, March 28 (Reuters) - Shares in Portugal's oil company Galp <GALP.LS> erased most of  the early losses on Friday to trade practically flat at 12.47 euros after the sale of a 7 percent stake in the company by Italy's ENI <ENI.MI> at a small discount.

ENI sold the stake at 12.1 euros, a discount of 3 percent from Thursday's closing price of Galp shares, pocketing 702 million euros.[ID:nI6N0MG029] Trading in Galp had been suspended on Friday before the announcement of the results of the sale. After falling 1 percent to 12.35 euros, Galp recovered most of the lost ground to trade at 12.47 euros at 10:01 a.m. (1001 GMT).